result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacquelyn Nicole Funk was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

RELEASING FUNDS - $250.00 to Clerk of Courts

3:50 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites plea agreement, defendant will plea to count 1 amended to Resisting an officer and to count 2.  DA concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 1 as amended and to count 2 as charged.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing argument by Atty Privat.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

Count 1 - 30 days county jail, with huber and out of county service.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to commence sentence.

Court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Count 2 - 3 days county jail - time served.

Court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Court adjourned at 4:03 p.m.

3:38 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Privat - has an offer and requests 30 days.  Court will set for plea & sentencing on May 4, 2015 at 3:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 3:39 p.m.
Status hearing on March 30, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
Status hearing on March 10, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Status hearing on March 9, 2015 at 02:00 pm.

2:44 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Privat - defendant will waive the preliminary hearing.  Defendant concurs.  

Court instructs the defendant regarding her right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives her right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.

State files an information with the court.  Attorney Privat and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Privat enters a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of the defendant.  Court will set for status hearing in 60 days - March 9, 2015 at 2:00 p.m.
